<root>
  <func>


    <title>cnc_t1info</title>



    <declare>
      <vc>
        <include>#include "fwlib32.h"</include>
        <prottype>FWLIBAPI short WINAPI cnc_t1info(unsigned short FlibHndl,short grp_num, short tool_num,ODBTLIFE4 *tinfo1); </prottype>
      </vc>
    </declare>



    <doc>
        <cmn>
            <p>
                Reads the tool information of the specified tool group and tool number.
            </p>
            <p>
                This function cannot be used with Series 15i or the "Tool life management B" option of Series 16i/18i,
                so use <a href="Toollife/cnc_rd1tlifedat2.htm" target="_parent">cnc_rd1tlifedat2</a> function instead of cnc_t1info function. 
            </p>
            <p>
                And this function can be only used by the tool number of under 4 digits,
                so use <a href="Toollife/cnc_rd1tlifedat2.htm" target="_parent">cnc_rd1tlifedat2</a> function in case of setting the tool number of over 4 digits with Series 30i. 
            </p>
        </cmn>

        <is>
        <cmn>
            <p>Reads the tool information of the specified tool group and tool number.</p>
            <p>And this function can be only used by the tool number of under 4 digits,
               so use <a href="Toollife/cnc_rd1tlifedat2.htm" target="_parent">cnc_rd1tlifedat2</a> function 
               in case of setting the tool number of over 4 digits.</p>
        </cmn>
        </is>
    </doc>



    <argument>
        <common>
            <vc>
                <item>
                    <name>FlibHndl</name>
                    <type>in</type>
                    <content>
                        <p>
                            Specify the library handle. See "<a href="handle.htm" target="_parent">Library handle</a>" for details.
                        </p>
                    </content>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>grp_num</name>
                    <type>in</type>
                    <content>
                        <p>
                            Specify the tool group number.
                        </p>
                    </content>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>tool_num</name>
                    <type>in</type>
                    <content>
                        <p>
                            Specify the tool number.
                        </p>
                    </content>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <name>tinfo1</name>
                    <type>out</type>
                    <content>
                        <p>
                            Pointer to the ODBTLIFE4 structure including the tool information.
                            The ODBTLIFE4 structure is as follows.
<pre>
typedef struct odbtlife4 {
    short  datano ;    /* Tool group number. */
    short  type ;      /* Tool number. */
    long   data ;      /* Tool information. */
} ODBTLIFE4 ;
</pre>
                            The tool information of the specified tool is stored in "tinfo1.data" with binary format as follows.
                            <br/>
                            <table border="1" class="dd">
                                <tr><th>tinfo1.data</th><th>Tool information</th></tr>
                                <tr><td>0</td><td>(refer to the following)</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>1</td><td>This tool is registered(available).</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>2</td><td>This tool has expired.</td></tr>
                                <tr><td>3</td><td>This tool was skipped.</td></tr>
                            </table>
                            <br/>
                            The currently used tool group and tool are referred by specifying <b>0</b>
                            in "grp_num" and "tool_num".
                            However, in case that any tool group number has never be specified
                            since power-on, <b>0</b> is stored.
                        </p>
                    </content>
                </item>
            </vc>
        </common>
    </argument>



    <errcode>
        <item class="xis">
            <name>EW_FUNC</name>
            <content>
                Unavailable(only Series 16i/18i)<br/>
                The tool life management B option is used.
            </content>
        </item>
        <item>
           <name>EW_NUMBER</name>
            <content>
                data number error<br/>
                The specification of tool group number(grp_num) is wrong.<br/>
            </content>
        </item>
        <item>
           <name>EW_ATTRIB</name>
            <content>
                data attribute error<br/>
                The specification of tool number(tool_num) is wrong.
            </content>
        </item>
        <item>
            <name>EW_NOOPT</name>
            <content>
                no option<br/>
                The tool life management function and the extended driver/library function are necessary.<br/>
            </content>
        </item>
    </errcode>



    <option>
        <hssb>
            <p>The extended driver/library function is necessary.</p>
        </hssb>

        <ethr>
            <p>The Ethernet function and the extended driver/library function are necessary.</p>
            <p>However, in case of Series 16i/18i/21i-B, 0i-B/C/D and 30i the required CNC option is as follows.</p>
            <p>When Embedded Ethernet is used,</p>
            <p><ul>above two optional functions are not required.</ul></p>
            <p>When Ethernet board is used,</p>
            <p><ul>only Ethernet function is required.</ul></p>
        </ethr>
        <need>
            <p>
                The tool life management function is necessary.
            </p>
        </need>
        <type>
            <li>Series 15<br/>
                <p>This function is influenced by 1024/512 pairs of the tool life management.</p>
            </li>
            <li>Series 16/18/21, 16i/18i/21i<br/>
                <p>This function is influenced by 512(M Series)/128(T Series) pairs of the tool life management.</p>
            </li>
            <li>Series 30i<br/>
                <p>This function is influenced by additional pairs number of the tool life management.</p>
                <table>
                    <tr> <td>the tool life management</td>        <td>:</td><td>256 pairs of the tool life management on whole system, both of M and T Series</td></tr>
                    <tr> <td>additional pairs number of the tool life management</td><td>:</td><td>1024 pairs of the tool life management on whole system, both of M and T Series</td></tr>
                </table>
            </li>
        </type>

        <is>
        <hssb>
              <p>The tool life management function and the extended driver/library function are necessary.</p>
              <p>And this function is influenced by additional pairs number of the tool life management.</p>
              <table>
                  <tr> <td>the tool life management</td><td>:</td>
                       <td>256 pairs of the tool life management on whole system, both of M and T Series</td></tr>
                  <tr> <td>additional pairs number of the tool life management</td><td>:</td>
                       <td>1024 pairs of the tool life management on whole system, both of M and T Series</td></tr>
              </table>
        </hssb>
        </is>
    </option>



    <parameter>
        <type>
            <ul type="disc">
